            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We also find structures that change in a different way…",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 48,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER2",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "<span style=\"font-weight: 600; color:white\">Disassembly & Recompartmentalization</span><br />Some structures present in interphase <i>disassemble</i> in order for a cell to divide. The structure’s protein components, however, don’t all disappear. Instead, they may <i>recompartmentalize</i> into a new structure or into a different structure that persists through mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 49,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER3",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can explore this with <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span>—a protein that forms a mesh cage on the inside of the <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">nuclear envelope</span>— and the <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">endoplasmic reticulum (ER)</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 50,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER4-trans",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "The <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">nuclear envelope</span> is a structure that disassembles during mitosis. During this process, <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> appears as a solid shell which then becomes ruffled and billows out.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 51,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER5-loop",
                "loop": true,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "fade",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "The <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">nuclear envelope</span> is a structure that disassembles during mitosis. During this process, <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> appears as a solid shell which then becomes ruffled and billows out.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 52,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER6-trans",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "By comparing the localization pattern of <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> with that of other structures using our Integrated Mitotic Stem Cell model, we notice that it mirrors the structure and behavior of the <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">ER</span> during mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 53,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER7-loop",
                "loop": true,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "fade",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "By comparing the localization pattern of <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> with that of other structures using our Integrated Mitotic Stem Cell model, we notice that it mirrors the structure and behavior of the <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">ER</span> during mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 54,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER8-trans",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This could be explained by the fact that <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> is a membrane-associated protein and that the outer nuclear membrane is contiguous with the <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">ER</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "media",
                        "mediaId": "ER-NuEnv-LaminB1-1",
                        "element": "",
                        "caption": "The <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">endoplasmic reticulum (ER)</span> is continuous with the nuclear envelope and the meshwork of lamina, comprised partially of <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span>, underlying the nuclear envelope</span>."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 55,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER8-loop",
