            "body": {
                "transition": "fade",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This could be explained by the fact that <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span> is a membrane-associated protein and that the outer nuclear membrane is contiguous with the <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">ER</span>.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "media",
                        "mediaId": "ER-NuEnv-LaminB1-1",
                        "element": "",
                        "caption": "The <span class=\"endoplasmic-reticulum\">endoplasmic reticulum (ER)</span> is continuous with the nuclear envelope and the meshwork of lamina, comprised partially of <span class=\"nuclear-envelope\">lamin B1</span>, underlying the nuclear envelope</span>."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
